email subject: Yoomin - [Google APM] Follow-up to your APM, University Graduate Application
email body: Hi Yoomin , Thanks for your interest in Google! We received your application for the Associate Product Manager, University Graduate role and would like to move forward. The first step is to complete a 45 minute preliminary screen with a Product Manager that will assess Product Insight, Strategic Insight & Analytical skills. Please review the next steps below to proceed: Schedule your first interview: O ur scheduling team ( google-interview-scheduling-team@google.com ) will be reaching out to collect your availability via a candidate portal. We understand that your schedule may not be able to accommodate the requested interview window. You’re able to provide availability outside of the requested window. Please check your spam folder if you haven’t heard from them within 48 business hours. Note: We hire on a rolling basis and would recommend you interview as soon as you’re available and feel prepared. Prepare for your interview: Review our attached APM Prep Guide. Review g.co/APM , the APM program site, along with the great program-specific content on the Google Students YouTube channel : Life of an APM: Meet a Google APM Alumni APM Program Overview APM YouTube Live: Recorded APM Prep Session Meet Product Managers at Google Google Resume Tips and Advice Review the important reminders at the end of this email What happens afterwards? Once your interview is completed, I’ll work on collecting your feedback (in some cases, this can take up to a week) and provide you with an email update. If successful at this interview stage, we’ll proceed with 3 more Google Meet interviews and a written assignment. The second round of interviews will cover the skills described in our APM Hiring Process video linked above and you’ll have the opportunity to connect with a recruiter before interviewing. Some Important Reminders: Given the strong interest we have seen in our APM internship, the expected duration of our hiring process will be approximately 8-12 weeks from your preliminary screen to the final offer. If you do have a confirmed offer deadline within that time frame, I would recommend reaching out to your recruiter with that company as early as possible to see if there is any possibility to get an extension so that you are able to fully explore your interest within Google! On my end, I will do my very best to ensure our process moves as quickly as possible. To provide you with as much flexibility as possible, we are offering a hybrid work model which may vary across roles and regions. Like most Googlers, this option means spending approximately three days in the office and two days wherever you work best. Participation in the internship program requires that you are located in the country to which you’ve applied for the duration of the internship program. If you’re located outside of the country and are unsure regarding work authorization, please mention this to your recruiter. Please be advised that if you are not able to be located in the country to which you’ve applied (either from the inability to obtain work authorization or the inability to travel/relocate), unfortunately, we will not be able to move forward with you as a candidate for the internship program. Best, Supraja ________________________________________ Supraja M Online Staffing Specialist Randstad Sourceright Supporting Google careers.google.com |Learn more about our candidate privacy policy.| If you received this communication by mistake, please don't forward it to anyone else (it may contain confidential or privileged information), please erase all copies of it, including all attachments, and please let the sender know it went to the wrong person. Thanks.

email subject: [Due in 4 days] Next Part of your Google Application: Google Hiring Assessment
email body: Hi Yoomin Choi, Thanks again for applying for a role at Google. The next step of the hiring process will be to complete the Google Hiring Assessment , which should take about 30 minutes. You may find your assessment link in your Candidate Portal or you may also copy and paste this link into your browser: https://www.google.com/about/careers/applications/dashboard Please complete the Google Hiring Assessment by 4:03 AM ET/1:03 AM PT on December 30. We can only consider your application for a role at Google if your assessment is completed by the deadline. The results of this assessment will determine if you're eligible to move forward with the hiring process. The Google Hiring Assessment questions, along with your responses, are for your eyes only. Do not forward or share them. Instructions Please complete this ~30-minute Google Hiring Assessment which will evaluate your work styles that are important to success at Google. After completing the Google Hiring Assessment, you will be presented with an optional module to share more about how you think and behave in work-related contexts. This section is completely voluntary and will have no impact on your application. If you need troubleshooting support with your assessment, please send an email to assessment-help@google.com and include your: First and Last Name Question or description of the issue and any relevant screenshots Accommodations We value inclusiveness and understand there are many ways to process information. If you require an accommodation due to a medical condition, disability, or neurodivergence, please send an email to assessment-help@google.com to request a specific accommodation or determine what options may be available. Let us know your accommodation needs before engaging in or completing the assessment. Accommodations include, but are not limited to: Extra time to complete the assessment Guidance on screen reader resources: Google Accessibility - built in screen reader Browser URL: https://support.google.com/accessibility/answer/7031755?hl=en#zippy=%2Cchoose-text-with-your-cursor Microsoft - Narrator Browser URL: https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/complete-guide-to-narrator-e4397a0d-ef4f-b386-d8ae-c172f109bdb1 There is no need to provide us with the nature of or reason for your request for accommodations at this time. Any information you do provide us regarding your health is provided with your explicit consent to our using such information to assess your accommodation request. You can withdraw that consent at any time by sending a subsequent email to assessment-help@google.com. However, if you withdraw consent before we have made an assessment we may not be able to provide you with an accommodation. Confidentiality: The information you provide in an accommodation request will only be reviewed by our global disability partner, EmployAbility, in order to assess and provide you with reasonable accommodations. Google does not require a diagnosis, treatment plan, or Government disability certificate. Thanks! Google Recruiting FAQs: Can I have an extension to complete the assessment? To keep our process fair, we ask that everyone complete the Google Hiring Assessment by the deadline. If you have a scheduling conflict that absolutely can't be moved, let us know as soon as possible by emailing assessment-help@google.com and we're happy to talk through options. Note: while we expect the GHA to take about 30 minutes to complete, you can spend as much time on it as you’d like up until your deadline noted above. Please note, if you hear from a recruiter before you've completed the Google Hiring Assessment, you'll still need to finish it by the deadline. Are there system/browser requirements to complete the Google Hiring Assessment? A consistent internet connection is essential for an optimal experience. We recommend testing your internet connection using our Measurement Lab tool to ensure it's stable. [Measurement Lab tool URL: https://www.google.com/search?q=internet%20speed%20test] Please use the latest version of one of these browsers: Chrome, Firefox, Microsoft Edge, Microsoft Internet Explorer, Safari. Additional questions? Check the Google Hiring Assessment FAQs . Google Hiring Assessment FAQ URL: https://services.google.com/fh/files/helpcenter/ghafaqs.pdf Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA. 94043 You received this email because of your recent application to Google.

email subject: Thank you for applying to Subsplash
email body: Yoomin, Thank you so much for your interest in Subsplash and for taking the time to apply for the Software Development Engineer I (Back-end) position. We just wanted to let you know that we received your application and that we're looking forward to reviewing it. If your application seems like a good fit for the position we will contact you soon! We are so humbled by the number of talented people who want to work with us! However, this does result in a large number of applications for every role we open up! We know this is a challenging time to be job-seeking, and we acknowledge you for the hard work you are putting in to find the perfect role for yourself! We know delays can be frustrating, and we are doing our best to review applications and provide updates as quickly as we can, but it may take some time before our tiny (but mighty!) hiring team can get back to you, so we thank you in advance for your patience with any possible delays. We acknowledge that applying for jobs can feel mysterious and you might be wondering what happens to your application after you apply. Well, we want you to know that we have a team of real (& awesome) people who carefully read through every application and they will follow up with you no matter what - no ghosting (or AI bots reviewing resumes) here 👻. We are excited about your candidacy! Heads up: email filtering can be tricky and filter out our email updates regarding the status of your application; we’d encourage you to keep an eye on your spam and promotion folder, just in case. ** Please note: Do not reply to this email. email body: Hi Yoomin , Thank you for your interest in our Netflix New Grad Software Engineer (2025) role! In order for your application to be reviewed, please complete this Airtable form . Your application will only be considered complete after you submit this form in conjunction with the application you already submitted on our Netflix Careers site. Please only complete the form once; duplicate submissions will not be considered. Due to the large volume of applications we receive, we're sorry that we're unable to personally follow up with each applicant. Our full recruiting process may take several weeks, so we kindly ask for your patience as we complete candidate reviews and interviews. In order to maintain a fair and equitable hiring process, we will not be able to accommodate very tight deadlines. For applicants selected to proceed, the interview process will begin with a CodeSignal pre-screen assessment based on the General Coding Framework. The results from this assessment will be used as just one additional data point to determine who will be invited to the interview rounds. The first round is a technical/coding interview with a software engineer, and then the final round consists of 3 interviews in a 3-hour block (1 problem-solving, 1 system design, 1 behavioral). Your advancement will be based on the feedback at each round. If you're selected to move forward, the next email you receive will come from CodeSignal; we strongly recommend adding no-reply@codesignal.com to your contacts to prevent spam filtering. Our goal is to reach out to candidates who are chosen for initial next steps within the next two to four weeks. If you haven’t heard from us by then, we may have reached interview capacity. Note that our New Grad interview process is designed to assess your generalist software engineering skills, coding fundamentals, and aptitude. Offers will be extended to join our 2025 New Grad class at Netflix, where we’ll have 2 start date options in Summer 2025 to centralize onboarding programming and training. All incoming New Grad Software Engineers will be matched to individual teams closer to their start dates, with their preferences, skills, and past experience taken into account. Thanks again, and good luck! -The Netflix Emerging Talent Team You received this email because you've applied, been referred, attended a event, or expressed interest in working at Netflix.
